body: "All current scale work (pm-9rxu) targets one workspace. The stated very-long-term vision — millions of items, thousands of concurrent agents — will in practice span many repositories and trackers. Unexplored axis: federation. Questions: workspace discovery in monorepos, stable cross-workspace ID references (workspace-qualified ids), read-side aggregation without merging git histories, claim/author identity across workspaces, and how the SDK exposes multi-workspace clients. This story is exploration-only (spike + ADR), deliberately parked at priority 4 until the SDK-first and scale-out initiatives land the single-workspace primitives it would compose.\n\n## Prior art (audit #15 follow-up — check existing packages first)\nThe unbraind org already ships pm-ops: multi-repo fleet operations for pm-cli (scan, policy, verify-release, report across many pm repositories). The federation spike/ADR must start from pm-ops as the read-side aggregation prior art and decide what belongs in core SDK primitives vs the pm-ops package (cross-workspace ids, deps, claims are the axes pm-ops does not cover today)."
